text: Gogunta is a village in West Godavari district of the Indian state of Andhra Pradesh. It is located in Pedapadu mandal of Eluru revenue division.. Nuzvid railway station is the nearest railway station. == Demographics == Census of India, Gogunta had a population of 708. The total population constitute, 348 males and 360 females with a sex ratio of 1034 females per 1000 males. 62 children are in the age group of 0–6 years with sex ratio of 1214. The average literacy rate stands at 67.80%. == References == Category:Villages in West Godavari district
